      "text": "The majority of community currencies seek to act as media of exchange for the users for which they are intended. This tries to remedy the problem of money becoming more scarce in times of austerity or crisis – when the national money supply shrinks or when much of it accumulates in the hands of a few at the expense of the many – even though, in many communities, the capacities to produce and contribute on the one hand, and demand and needs on the other hand, remain the same. As an alternative medium of exchange, a community currency can connect supply and demand when mainstream money is scarce."
